    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="740"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-06T19:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Your August 6, 1 a.m. Ascertain whether British Government would be willing to
                    enter such agreement. Other European nations at war have been asked whether they
                    are willing to enter such arrangements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
